244
00:27:19,383 --> 00:27:22,103
There was a time when men were kind,>>

245
00:27:24,303 --> 00:27:26,603
And their voices were soft,>>

246
00:27:29,003 --> 00:27:31,103
And their words inviting.

247
00:27:33,503 --> 00:27:37,203
There was a time when love was blind,>>

248
00:27:37,703 --> 00:27:40,303
And the world was a song,>>

249
00:27:42,003 --> 00:27:45,803
And the song was exciting.

250
00:27:47,103 --> 00:27:49,803
There was a time...>>

251
00:27:55,803 --> 00:28:00,603
when it all went wrong...>>

252
00:28:14,903 --> 00:28:21,003
I dreamed a dream in time gone by,>>

253
00:28:22,703 --> 00:28:27,003
When hope was high and life worth living.

254
00:28:30,003 --> 00:28:37,103
I dreamed that love would never die,>>

255
00:28:37,703 --> 00:28:42,003
I dreamed that God would be forgiving.

256
00:28:45,703 --> 00:28:52,503
Then I was young and unafraid,>>

257
00:28:53,303 --> 00:28:59,603
And dreams were made and used and wasted.

258
00:29:01,403 --> 00:29:08,503
There was no ransom to be paid,>>

259
00:29:08,703 --> 00:29:14,003
No song unsung, no wine, untasted.

260
00:29:17,303 --> 00:29:23,503
But the tigers come at night,>>

261
00:29:25,203 --> 00:29:31,603
With their voices soft as thunder,>>

262
00:29:32,703 --> 00:29:38,603
As they tear your hope apart,>>

263
00:29:40,403 --> 00:29:56,903
And they turn your dream to shame.

264
00:29:57,903 --> 00:30:03,303
He slept a summer by my side,>>

265
00:30:03,903 --> 00:30:09,103
He filled my days with endless wonder...>>

266
00:30:11,303 --> 00:30:18,103
He took my childhood in his stride,>>

267
00:30:18,303 --> 00:30:22,903
But he was gone when autumn came!

268
00:30:28,203 --> 00:30:34,203
And still I dream he'll come to me,>>

269
00:30:34,403 --> 00:30:39,503
That we will live the years together,>>

270
00:30:41,503 --> 00:30:47,303
But there are dreams that cannot be,>>

271
00:30:47,503 --> 00:30:52,803
And there are storms we cannot weather!

272
00:30:58,403 --> 00:31:01,103
I had a dream my life would be>>

273
00:31:03,703 --> 00:31:08,003
So different from this hell I'm living,>>

274
00:31:08,203 --> 00:31:14,503
So different now from what it seemed...>>

275
00:31:18,703 --> 00:31:42,903
Now life has killed the dream I dreamed...>>

276
00:32:12,692 --> 00:32:15,712
9."Fantine's Arrest" (Fantine, Javert, Valjean)>>

277
00:32:15,722 --> 00:32:19,742
You've got some nerve, you little slut You've got some gall.

279
00:32:26,442 --> 00:32:29,442
I guarantee, I'll make you suffer>>

280
00:32:29,942 --> 00:32:33,642
I beg you, don't report me sir I'll do whatever you may want>>

282
00:32:37,466 --> 00:32:40,086
Tell me quickly what's the story>>

283
00:32:40,286 --> 00:32:42,286
Who saw what and why and where>>

284
00:32:42,386 --> 00:32:46,286
Let him give a full description Let him answer to Javert!

285
00:32:46,486 --> 00:32:50,786
Javert, would you believe it I was lost here in the dark>>

286
00:32:50,986 --> 00:32:55,786
When this prostitute attacked me You can see she left her mark>>

287
00:32:56,286 --> 00:33:00,786
She will answer for her actions If you make a full report>>

288
00:33:00,986 --> 00:33:05,586
You may rest assured, M'sieur, she will answer to the court.

289
00:33:05,786 --> 00:33:11,186
There's a child who sorely needs me Please M'sieur, she's but that high>>

290
00:33:11,386 --> 00:33:18,786
Holy God, is there no mercy? If I go to jail she'll die!

291
00:33:18,986 --> 00:33:24,386
I have heard such protestations Every day for 20 years>>

292
00:33:24,586 --> 00:33:29,186
Let's have no more explanations Save your breath and save your tears>>

293
00:33:29,386 --> 00:33:35,986
`Honest work, just reward, That's the way to please the Lord.'>>

294
00:33:36,686 --> 00:33:39,786
A moment of your time, Javert I do believe this woman's tale>>

295
00:33:39,786 --> 00:33:41,686
M'sieur le Mayor>>

296
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:45,886
You've done your duty, let her be She needs a doctor, not a jail>>

297
00:33:45,886 --> 00:33:49,486
But M'sieur Mayor! Can this be?

298
00:33:49,486 --> 00:33:57,086
Where will she end? This child without a friend?

299
00:34:00,386 --> 00:34:02,986
I've seen your face before>>

300
00:34:06,486 --> 00:34:10,386
Show me some way to help you>>

301
00:34:12,686 --> 00:34:16,186
How have you come to grief>>

302
00:34:16,386 --> 00:34:20,186
In a place such as this?

303
00:34:22,686 --> 00:34:26,286
M'sieur, don't mock me now, I pray>>

304
00:34:27,986 --> 00:34:31,886
It's hard enough I've lost my pride>>

305
00:34:34,186 --> 00:34:40,886
You let your foreman send me away>>

306
00:34:40,886 --> 00:34:47,386
Yes, you were there, and turned aside>>

307
00:34:55,086 --> 00:34:57,986
I never did no wrong>>

308
00:34:57,986 --> 00:34:59,886
Is it true, what I have done?

309
00:35:00,086 --> 00:35:05,386
My daughter's close to dying... To an innocent soul?

310
00:35:05,586 --> 00:35:10,686
If there's a God above Had I only known then...>>

311
00:35:10,886 --> 00:35:15,286
He'd let me die instead>>

312
00:35:16,686 --> 00:35:21,686
In His name my task has just begun>>

313
00:35:23,886 --> 00:35:26,786
I will take her to the hospital.

314
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:26,700
10."Who Am I? / The Trial" (Valjean)>>

315
00:37:26,816 --> 00:37:31,136
He thinks that man is me without a second glance!

316
00:37:31,336 --> 00:37:36,036
The stranger they have found This man could be my chance!

317
00:37:36,736 --> 00:37:40,636
Why should I save his hide? Why should I right this wrong?

318
00:37:41,536 --> 00:37:46,036
When I have come so far And struggled for so long?

319
00:37:48,236 --> 00:37:52,436
If I speak, I am condemned.

320
00:37:54,436 --> 00:38:00,836
If I stay silent, I am damned!

321
00:38:01,036 --> 00:38:04,936
I am the master of hundreds of workers. They all look to me.

322
00:38:06,336 --> 00:38:10,936
How can I abandon them? How would they live if I am not free?

323
00:38:13,736 --> 00:38:16,936
If I speak, they are condemned.

324
00:38:19,036 --> 00:38:27,336
If I stay silent, I am damned!

325
00:38:32,036 --> 00:38:34,136
Who am I?

326
00:38:36,036 --> 00:38:38,536
Can I condemn this man to slavery>>

327
00:38:39,936 --> 00:38:42,836
Pretend I do not feel his agony>>

328
00:38:45,036 --> 00:38:49,336
This innocent who bears my face Who goes to judgement in my place>>

329
00:38:49,736 --> 00:38:51,036
Who am I?

330
00:38:51,436 --> 00:38:54,136
Can I conceal myself for evermore?

331
00:38:55,336 --> 00:38:58,336
Pretend I'm not the man I was before?

332
00:39:00,336 --> 00:39:04,736
And must my name until I die Be no more than an alibi?

333
00:39:04,936 --> 00:39:06,336
Must I lie?

334
00:39:06,536 --> 00:39:09,236
How can I ever face my fellow men?

335
00:39:10,236 --> 00:39:12,936
How can I ever face myself again?

336
00:39:14,836 --> 00:39:19,236
My soul belongs to God, I know I made that bargain long ago>>

337
00:39:19,736 --> 00:39:22,836
He gave me hope when hope was gone>>

338
00:39:23,336 --> 00:39:28,736
He gave me strength to journey on>>

339
00:39:28,936 --> 00:39:36,936
Who am I? Who am I?

340
00:39:38,136 --> 00:39:40,036
Jean Valjean!

341
00:39:44,136 --> 00:39:51,636
And so Your Honor, you see it's true This man bears no more guilt than you!

342
00:39:52,336 --> 00:39:54,936
Who am I?

343
00:39:56,336 --> 00:40:02,536
24601!

344
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:28,000
11."Come to Me (Fantine's Death)" (Fantine, Valjean)>>

345
00:40:28,244 --> 00:40:32,764
Cosette, it's turned so cold>>

346
00:40:36,264 --> 00:40:41,464
Cosette, it's past your bedtime>>

347
00:40:44,018 --> 00:40:48,938
You've played the day away>>

348
00:40:49,738 --> 00:40:56,238
And soon it will be night.

349
00:40:58,938 --> 00:41:08,938
Come to me, Cosette, the light is fading>>

350
00:41:11,338 --> 00:41:19,638
Don't you see the evening star appearing?

351
00:41:23,638 --> 00:41:31,038
Come to me, and rest against my shoulder>>

352
00:41:33,038 --> 00:41:40,038
How fast the minutes fly away and every minute colder.

353
00:41:41,938 --> 00:41:47,238
Dear Fantine, Cosette will be here soon>>

354
00:41:49,238 --> 00:41:54,638
Dear Fantine, she will be by your side>>

355
00:41:56,738 --> 00:42:03,038
Come Cosette, my child. Where did you go?

356
00:42:05,538 --> 00:42:07,838
Be at peace...>>

357
00:42:10,538 --> 00:42:14,138
Be at peace evermore...>>

358
00:42:14,338 --> 00:42:16,938
My Cosette...>>

359
00:42:17,638 --> 00:42:21,538
Shall live in my protection>>

360
00:42:24,438 --> 00:42:26,338
Take her now>>

361
00:42:26,538 --> 00:42:30,038
Your child will want for nothing>>

362
00:42:32,338 --> 00:42:39,838
Good M'sieur, you come from God in Heaven.

363
00:42:43,038 --> 00:42:49,238
Tell her I love her.

364
00:42:50,638 --> 00:42:58,638
And I'll see her when I wake...>>

365
00:43:16,900 --> 00:43:20,000
12."The Confrontation" (Javert, Valjean)>>

366
00:43:20,217 --> 00:43:23,337
Valjean, at last,>>

367
00:43:23,537 --> 00:43:26,437
We see each other plain>>

368
00:43:26,637 --> 00:43:28,937
`M'sieur le Mayor,'>>

369
00:43:29,137 --> 00:43:32,937
You'll wear a different chain!

370
00:43:32,937 --> 00:43:35,737
Before you say another word, Javert>>

371
00:43:36,037 --> 00:43:38,337
Before you chain me up like a slave again>>

372
00:43:38,837 --> 00:43:44,037
Listen to me! There is something I must do.

373
00:43:44,837 --> 00:43:47,637
This woman leaves behind a suffering child.

374
00:43:48,037 --> 00:43:50,637
There is none but me who can intercede,>>

375
00:43:51,037 --> 00:43:55,537
In Mercy's name, 3 days are all I need.

376
00:43:57,037 --> 00:43:59,737
Then I'll return, I pledge my word.

377
00:44:00,037 --> 00:44:02,637
Then I'll return... You must think me mad!

378
00:44:02,937 --> 00:44:05,637
I've hunted you across the years>>

379
00:44:05,837 --> 00:44:08,537
A man like you can never change>>

380
00:44:08,737 --> 00:44:14,337
A man such as you.

381
00:44:14,837 --> 00:44:17,137
Believe of me what you will>>

382
00:44:17,737 --> 00:44:20,637
There is a duty that I'm sworn to do>>

383
00:44:20,837 --> 00:44:23,637
You know nothing of my life>>

384
00:44:23,837 --> 00:44:26,337
All I did was steal some bread>>

385
00:44:26,537 --> 00:44:29,037
You know nothing of the world>>

386
00:44:29,237 --> 00:44:32,037
You would sooner see me dead>>

387
00:44:32,237 --> 00:44:37,637
But not before I see this justice done>>

388
00:44:37,837 --> 00:44:40,437
I am warning you Javert>>

389
00:44:40,637 --> 00:44:43,137
I'm a stronger man by far>>

390
00:44:43,337 --> 00:44:45,737
There is power in me yet>>

391
00:44:45,937 --> 00:44:49,337
My race is not yet run>>

392
00:44:49,537 --> 00:44:51,537
You know nothing of Javert>>

393
00:44:51,737 --> 00:44:53,937
I was born inside a jail>>

394
00:44:54,137 --> 00:44:56,637
I was born with scum like you>>

395
00:44:56,837 --> 00:45:00,037
I am from the gutter too!

396
00:45:21,100 --> 00:45:24,200
13."Castle on a Cloud" (Young Cosette)>>

397
00:45:24,603 --> 00:45:28,823
There is a castle on a cloud,>>

398
00:45:29,523 --> 00:45:33,623
I like to go there in my sleep,>>

399
00:45:34,223 --> 00:45:38,623
Aren't any floors for me to sweep,>>

400
00:45:39,023 --> 00:45:43,123
Not in my castle on a cloud.

401
00:45:43,723 --> 00:45:47,823
There is a lady all in white,>>

402
00:45:48,023 --> 00:45:51,523
Holds me and sings a lullaby,>>

403
00:45:51,723 --> 00:45:55,823
She's nice to see and she's soft to touch,>>

404
00:45:56,123 --> 00:46:01,523
She says "Cosette, I love you very much.">>

405
00:46:01,923 --> 00:46:06,323
I know a place where no one's lost,>>

406
00:46:06,823 --> 00:46:11,023
I know a place where no one cries,>>

407
00:46:11,723 --> 00:46:16,023
Crying at all is not allowed,>>

408
00:46:16,523 --> 00:46:21,423
Not in my castle on a cloud.

409
00:46:22,823 --> 00:46:27,723
Now look who's here The little madam herself!

410
00:46:28,323 --> 00:46:33,623
Pretending once again she's been `so awfully good,'>>

411
00:46:33,823 --> 00:46:37,623
Better not let me catch you slacking Better not catch my eye!

412
00:46:37,823 --> 00:46:41,723
10 rotten francs your mother sends me What is that going to buy?

413
00:46:42,723 --> 00:46:46,723
Now take that pail My little `Mademoiselle'>>

414
00:46:46,923 --> 00:46:49,623
And go and draw some water from the well!

415
00:46:51,023 --> 00:46:53,323
We should never have taken you in in the first place>>

416
00:46:53,623 --> 00:46:54,823
How stupid the things that we do!

417
00:46:54,823 --> 00:46:57,023
Like mother like daughter, the scum of the street.

418
00:46:59,623 --> 00:47:03,423
Mamma! Eponine, come my dear, Eponine, let me see you>>

419
00:47:03,423 --> 00:47:05,423
You look very well in that new little blue hat>>

420
00:47:07,823 --> 00:47:10,023
There's some little girls who know how to behave>>

421
00:47:10,423 --> 00:47:11,623
And they know what to wear>>

422
00:47:11,623 --> 00:47:13,423
And I'm saying thank heaven for that.

423
00:47:14,723 --> 00:47:18,923
Still there Cosette? Your tears will do you no good!

424
00:47:19,123 --> 00:47:23,223
I told you fetch some water from the well in the wood!

425
00:47:23,423 --> 00:47:27,523
Please do not send me out alone>>

426
00:47:28,123 --> 00:47:31,923
Not in the darkness on my own!

427
00:47:49,303 --> 00:47:52,303
14."Master of the House" (Thénardier and Mme., Inn Patrons)>>

428
00:47:54,850 --> 00:47:58,370
My band of soaks>>

429
00:47:58,870 --> 00:48:01,870
My den of dissolutes>>

430
00:48:02,670 --> 00:48:10,870
My dirty jokes, my always pissed as newts.

431
00:48:11,670 --> 00:48:15,870
My sons of whores>>

432
00:48:19,270 --> 00:48:22,670
Spent their lives in my inn>>

433
00:48:25,670 --> 00:48:29,370
Homing pigeons homing in>>

434
00:48:29,870 --> 00:48:33,670
They fly through my doors>>

435
00:48:37,070 --> 00:48:40,270
And their money's as good as yours>>

436
00:48:44,470 --> 00:48:48,170
Welcome, M'sieur Sit yourself down>>

437
00:48:48,370 --> 00:48:51,670
And meet the best Innkeeper in town>>

438
00:48:53,270 --> 00:48:56,670
As for the rest, All of 'em crooks>>

439
00:48:56,870 --> 00:48:59,770
Rooking their guests And cooking the books.

440
00:49:02,070 --> 00:49:08,670
Seldom do you see Honest men like me>>

441
00:49:08,870 --> 00:49:15,070
A gent of good intent Who's content to be>>

442
00:49:15,570 --> 00:49:18,470
Master of the house Doling out the charm>>

443
00:49:18,670 --> 00:49:21,470
Ready with a handshake And an open palm>>

444
00:49:21,670 --> 00:49:24,470
Tells a saucy tale Makes a little stir>>

445
00:49:24,670 --> 00:49:27,270
Customers appreciate a bon-viveur>>

446
00:49:27,470 --> 00:49:32,770
Glad to do a friend a favor Doesn't cost me to be nice>>

447
00:49:33,370 --> 00:49:37,770
But nothing gets you nothing Everything has got a little price!

448
00:49:38,970 --> 00:49:41,870
Master of the house Keeper of the zoo>>

449
00:49:42,070 --> 00:49:44,770
Ready to relieve 'em Of a sou or two>>

450
00:49:44,970 --> 00:49:47,570
Watering the wine Making up the weight>>

451
00:49:47,770 --> 00:49:50,570
Pickin' up their knick-knacks When they can't see straight>>

452
00:49:50,770 --> 00:49:55,870
Everybody loves a landlord Everybody's bosom friend>>

453
00:49:56,070 --> 00:49:59,970
I do whatever pleases Jesus! Won't I bleed 'em in the end!

454
00:50:00,370 --> 00:50:03,270
Master of the house Quick to catch yer eye>>

455
00:50:03,470 --> 00:50:06,170
Never wants a passerby To pass him by>>

456
00:50:06,370 --> 00:50:09,070
Servant to the poor Butler to the great>>

457
00:50:09,270 --> 00:50:11,970
Comforter, philosopher, And lifelong mate!

458
00:50:12,170 --> 00:50:16,970
Everybody's boon companion Everybody's chaperone>>

459
00:50:17,470 --> 00:50:21,270
But lock up your valises Jesus! Won't I skin you to the bone!

460
00:50:21,970 --> 00:50:24,870
Food beyond compare Food beyond belief>>

461
00:50:25,070 --> 00:50:27,870
Mix it in a mincer And pretend it's beef>>

462
00:50:28,070 --> 00:50:30,770
Kidney of a horse Liver of a cat>>

463
00:50:30,970 --> 00:50:33,670
Filling up the sausages With this and that>>

464
00:50:33,870 --> 00:50:39,070
Residents are more than welcome Bridal suite is occupied>>

465
00:50:39,270 --> 00:50:43,970
Reasonable charges Plus some little extras on the side!

466
00:50:45,070 --> 00:50:48,170
Charge 'em for the lice Extra for the mice>>

467
00:50:48,370 --> 00:50:51,070
2% for looking in the mirror twice>>

468
00:50:51,270 --> 00:50:53,870
Here a little slice There a little cut>>

469
00:50:54,070 --> 00:50:56,770
3% for sleeping with the window shut>>

470
00:50:56,970 --> 00:50:59,470
When it comes to fixing prices>>

471
00:50:59,670 --> 00:51:03,770
There are a lot of tricks he knows How it all increases>>

472
00:51:03,770 --> 00:51:08,170
All those bits and pieces Jesus! It's amazing how it grows!

473
00:51:17,870 --> 00:51:22,070
I used to dream That I would meet a prince>>

474
00:51:22,470 --> 00:51:28,870
But God Almighty, Have you seen what's happened since?

475
00:51:30,570 --> 00:51:35,670
`Master of the house?' Isn't worth me spit!

476
00:51:35,870 --> 00:51:40,270
`Comforter, philosopher' - and lifelong shit!

477
00:51:40,870 --> 00:51:45,770
Cunning little brain Regular Voltaire>>

478
00:51:45,970 --> 00:51:51,070
Thinks he's quite a lover But there's not much there>>

479
00:51:51,270 --> 00:51:58,370
What a cruel trick of nature Landed me with such a louse>>

480
00:51:58,570 --> 00:52:02,470
God knows how I've lasted Living with this bastard in the house!

481
00:52:03,270 --> 00:52:05,870
Master of the house. Master and a half!

482
00:52:06,070 --> 00:52:08,770
Comforter, philosopher Ah, don't make me laugh!

483
00:52:08,970 --> 00:52:14,570
Servant to the poor. Butler to the great. Hypocrite and toady and inebriate!

484
00:52:14,770 --> 00:52:20,170
Everybody bless the landlord! Everybody bless his spouse!

485
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:23,570
Everybody raise a glass>>

486
00:52:26,070 --> 00:52:30,270
Everybody raise a glass to the master of the house!

487
00:52:58,523 --> 00:53:03,443
Hush now. Do not be afraid of me.

488
00:53:04,643 --> 00:53:08,843
Don't hide. Show me where you live>>

489
00:53:09,943 --> 00:53:13,543
Tell me my chid. What is your name?

490
00:53:15,143 --> 00:53:17,743
I'm called Cosette>>

491
00:53:22,843 --> 00:53:24,743
Can I help you with your bucket?

492
00:53:35,041 --> 00:53:37,061
I've found her wandering in the wood.

493
00:53:37,061 --> 00:53:39,961
This little child, I've found her trembling in the shadows.

494
00:53:40,661 --> 00:53:42,861
And I am here to help Cosette>>

495
00:53:43,061 --> 00:53:45,861
I will settle any debt you may think proper>>

496
00:53:46,261 --> 00:53:50,761
I will pay what I must pay>>

497
00:53:51,561 --> 00:53:54,661
to take Cosette away>>

498
00:53:59,661 --> 00:54:03,061
This is a duty I must>>

499
00:54:05,861 --> 00:54:09,061
There is a promess I have made>>

500
00:54:09,261 --> 00:54:13,661
->>

501
00:54:15,261 --> 00:54:18,661
->>

502
00:54:22,461 --> 00:54:25,261
And your mother is with God>>

503
00:54:28,861 --> 00:54:32,061
Certainly is rebirthed>>

504
00:54:34,861 --> 00:54:38,761
And I speek here with her voice>>

505
00:54:40,561 --> 00:54:46,761
And I stand here in her place>>

506
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:53,061
And from ths day and evermore>>

507
00:54:55,161 --> 00:54:58,661
Cosette shall live in my protection>>

508
00:54:59,461 --> 00:55:04,761
You are very wellcome here. I will not forget our vow>>

509
00:55:04,761 --> 00:55:06,961
Take a drink. Take a chair.

510
00:55:07,161 --> 00:55:11,961
Cosette shall have a father now>>

511
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:15,100
16."The Bargain" (Thénardier and Mme., Valjean, Young Cosette)>>

512
00:55:15,271 --> 00:55:19,291
What to do? What to say?

513
00:55:19,491 --> 00:55:23,191
Shall you carry our treasure away?

514
00:55:23,391 --> 00:55:27,191
What a gem! What a pearl!

515
00:55:27,791 --> 00:55:31,191
Beyond rubies is our little girl!

516
00:55:31,391 --> 00:55:35,191
How can we talk of debt?

517
00:55:35,391 --> 00:55:42,391
Let's not haggle for darling Colette! Cosette!

518
00:55:43,691 --> 00:55:47,491
Dear Fantine, gone to rest...>>

519
00:55:47,991 --> 00:55:51,491
Have we done for her child what is best? I think so.

520
00:55:51,691 --> 00:55:55,391
Shared our bread. Shared each bone.

521
00:55:55,591 --> 00:56:01,691
Treated her like she's one of our own! Like our own, Monsieur!

522
00:56:03,091 --> 00:56:08,191
Your feelings do you credit, sir And I will ease the parting blow>>

523
00:56:08,391 --> 00:56:12,491
Let us not talk of bargains or bones or greed>>

524
00:56:13,391 --> 00:56:18,091
Now, may I say, we are agreed?

525
00:56:18,291 --> 00:56:25,691
That would quite fit the bill If she hadn't so often been ill>>

526
00:56:26,391 --> 00:56:33,191
Little dear, cost us dear Medicines are expensive, M'sieur>>

527
00:56:33,791 --> 00:56:37,291
Not that we begrudged a sou>>

528
00:56:38,091 --> 00:56:42,791
It's no more than we Christians must do!

529
00:56:44,291 --> 00:56:47,791
No more words. Here's your price.

530
00:56:47,991 --> 00:56:51,891
Fifteen hundred for your sacrifice.

531
00:56:52,091 --> 00:56:55,291
Come, Cosette, say goodbye>>

532
00:56:55,691 --> 00:56:59,291
Let us seek out some friendlier sky.

533
00:56:59,991 --> 00:57:03,091
Thank you both for Cosette>>

534
00:57:03,291 --> 00:57:07,791
It won't take you too long to forget.

535
00:57:09,691 --> 00:57:13,791
Farewell Cojette! Cosette.

536
00:58:19,100 --> 00:58:22,300
17."Suddenly" (Valjean, new song)>>

537
00:58:22,586 --> 00:58:29,406
Suddenly I'm here Suddenly it starts>>

538
00:58:29,706 --> 00:58:34,906
When two anxious hearts beat as one.

539
00:58:37,206 --> 00:58:43,506
Yesterday I was alone Today you walk beside me>>

540
00:58:44,406 --> 00:58:50,106
Something still unclear Something not yet here>>

541
00:58:50,806 --> 00:58:52,806
Has begun.

542
00:58:58,006 --> 00:59:03,606
Suddenly the world Seems a different place>>

543
00:59:04,306 --> 00:59:08,206
Somehow full of grace And delight.

544
00:59:10,906 --> 00:59:15,106
How was I to know That so much love>>

545
00:59:15,306 --> 00:59:17,706
Was held inside me?

546
00:59:18,806 --> 00:59:27,306
But her past is gone Now we are long through the night.

547
00:59:28,306 --> 00:59:34,106
How was I to know at last That happiness can come so fast?

548
00:59:34,306 --> 00:59:39,806
Trusting me the way you do Im so afraid of failing you>>

549
00:59:40,006 --> 00:59:45,506
Just a child who cannot know That danger follows where I go>>

550
00:59:45,706 --> 00:59:52,806
There are shadows everywhere And memories I cannot share>>

551
00:59:54,406 --> 01:00:00,106
Nevermore alone Nevermore apart>>

552
01:00:02,906 --> 01:00:05,106
You have warmed my heart Like the sun.

553
01:00:07,706 --> 01:00:15,206
You have brought the gift of life And love so long denied me.

554
01:00:16,306 --> 01:00:20,706
Suddenly I see What I could not see>>

555
01:00:23,406 --> 01:00:34,406
Something suddenly Has begun>>

556
01:03:47,400 --> 01:03:50,500
18."Stars" (Javert)>>

557
01:03:50,778 --> 01:03:59,498
There, out in the darkness A fugitive running>>

558
01:04:00,698 --> 01:04:09,098
Fallen from God Fallen from grace>>

559
01:04:09,298 --> 01:04:14,698
God be my witness I never shall yield>>

560
01:04:15,598 --> 01:04:22,398
Till we come face to face>>

561
01:04:23,298 --> 01:04:30,598
He knows his way in the dark Mine is the way of the Lord>>

562
01:04:30,798 --> 01:04:37,798
And those who follow the path of the righteous Shall have their reward>>

563
01:04:38,198 --> 01:04:47,298
And if they fall, as Lucifer fell The flame, the sword!

564
01:04:47,498 --> 01:04:53,298
Stars In your multitudes>>

565
01:04:53,998 --> 01:05:00,198
Scarce to be counted Filling the darkness>>

566
01:05:01,198 --> 01:05:08,198
With order and light You are the sentinels>>

567
01:05:08,598 --> 01:05:10,598
Silent and sure>>

568
01:05:11,598 --> 01:05:17,698
Keeping watch in the night>>

569
01:05:18,898 --> 01:05:21,298
You know your place in the sky>>

570
01:05:22,298 --> 01:05:25,298
You hold your course and your aim>>

571
01:05:25,298 --> 01:05:29,298
And each in your season Returns and returns>>

572
01:05:29,498 --> 01:05:32,998
And is always the same>>

573
01:05:33,398 --> 01:05:36,898
And if you fall as Lucifer fell>>

574
01:05:37,098 --> 01:05:41,598
You fall in flame!

575
01:05:41,798 --> 01:05:46,298
And so it has been and so it is written>>

576
01:05:46,498 --> 01:05:49,798
On the doorway to paradise>>

577
01:05:49,998 --> 01:05:52,798
That those who falter and those who fall>>

578
01:05:53,198 --> 01:05:56,898
Must pay the price!

579
01:06:02,798 --> 01:06:08,598
Lord let me find him That I may see him>>

580
01:06:09,498 --> 01:06:15,598
Safe behind bars I will never rest>>

581
01:06:16,798 --> 01:06:22,598
Till then This I swear>>

582
01:06:22,798 --> 01:06:34,098
This I swear by the stars!

583
01:07:09,200 --> 01:07:12,200
19."Look Down" (People)>>

584
01:07:12,439 --> 01:07:17,759
Look down and see the beggars at your feet>>

585
01:07:18,159 --> 01:07:24,159
Look down and show some mercy if you can>>

586
01:07:24,359 --> 01:07:29,659
Look down and see the sweepings of the street>>

587
01:07:29,859 --> 01:07:35,959
Look down, look down, Upon your fellow man!

588
01:07:36,559 --> 01:07:41,859
'Ow do you do? My name's Gavroche. These are my people. Here's my patch.

589
01:07:42,059 --> 01:07:47,759
Not much to look at, nothing posh Nothing that you'd call up to scratch.

590
01:07:47,959 --> 01:07:53,259
This is my school, my high society Here in the slums of Saint Michele>>

591
01:07:53,459 --> 01:07:58,759
We live on crumbs of humble piety Tough on the teeth, but what the hell!

592
01:07:58,959 --> 01:08:01,559
Think you're poor? Think you're free?

593
01:08:01,759 --> 01:08:04,359
Follow me! Follow me!

594
01:08:04,559 --> 01:08:09,759
Look down and show some mercy if you can>>

595
01:08:09,959 --> 01:08:15,659
Look down, look down, upon your fellow man!

596
01:08:15,859 --> 01:08:21,459
There was a time we killed the king. We've tried to change the world too fast>>

597
01:08:21,659 --> 01:08:27,159
Now we have got another king He's no better than the last>>

598
01:08:27,359 --> 01:08:32,859
This is the land of full liberty Now when we fight, we fight for great.

599
01:08:33,059 --> 01:08:38,359
Here is the thing about equality Even if we could when we're dead>>

600
01:08:38,559 --> 01:08:44,159
Take your place. Take your chance Vive la France. Vive la France!

601
01:08:44,328 --> 01:08:49,048
Look down and show some mercy if you can>>

602
01:08:49,248 --> 01:08:55,448
Look down, look down, upon your fellow man!

603
01:08:55,648 --> 01:08:58,148
When's it gonna end? When we gonna live?

604
01:08:58,348 --> 01:09:00,748
Something's gotta happen now or Something's gonna give>>

605
01:09:00,948 --> 01:09:03,648
It'll come, it'll come, it'll come>>

606
01:09:03,648 --> 01:09:08,948
Where are the leaders of the land? Where is the king who runs this show?

607
01:09:09,148 --> 01:09:14,048
Only one man - general Lamarque Speaks for the people here below.

608
01:09:14,248 --> 01:09:19,548
Lamarque is ill and fading fast! Won't last the week out, so they say.

609
01:09:19,548 --> 01:09:25,348
With all the anger in the land How long before the judgement day?

610
01:09:25,348 --> 01:09:29,648
Before we cut the fat ones down to size?

611
01:09:30,948 --> 01:09:36,748
Before the barricades arise?

612
01:09:46,707 --> 01:09:48,327
Marius. Grandfather.

613
01:09:48,327 --> 01:09:53,627
Have you any idea of the shame you bring on our family?

614
01:10:01,527 --> 01:10:06,827
Vive la France!

615
01:11:19,200 --> 01:11:22,400
20."The Robbery" (Thénardier,  Marius, Éponine, Valjean)>>

616
01:11:22,620 --> 01:11:27,440
Everyone here, you know your place Brujon, Babet, Claquesous>>

617
01:11:28,040 --> 01:11:33,040
You, Montparnasse, watch for the law With Eponine take care>>

618
01:11:33,240 --> 01:11:37,340
You turn on the tears No mistakes, my dears>>

619
01:11:39,340 --> 01:11:47,840
Please m'sieur, come this way Here's a child that ain't eaten today.

620
01:11:48,040 --> 01:11:56,540
Save a life, spare a sou God rewards all the good that you do.

621
01:11:57,440 --> 01:12:06,640
Wait a bit. Know that face. Ain't the world a remarkable place?

622
01:12:07,740 --> 01:12:15,340
Men like me don't forget You're the bastard that borrowed Colette! Cosette!

623
01:12:15,540 --> 01:12:21,440
What is this? Are you mad? No, Monsieur, you don't know what you say!

624
01:12:21,440 --> 01:12:24,740
You know me, you know me. I'm a con, just like you.

625
01:12:29,303 --> 01:12:34,003
It's the police! Disappear! Run for it! It's Javert!

626
01:12:34,203 --> 01:12:36,303
21."Javert's Intervention" (Javert, Thénardier)>>

627
01:12:36,303 --> 01:12:38,903
Another brawl in this square Another stink in the air!

628
01:12:38,903 --> 01:12:41,603
Was there a witness to this? Well, let him speak to Javert!

629
01:12:41,603 --> 01:12:45,403
M'sieur, the streets are not safe, But let these vermin beware>>

630
01:12:45,603 --> 01:12:47,803
We'll see that justice is done!

631
01:12:48,603 --> 01:12:53,903
Look upon this fine collection Crawled from underneath a stone>>

632
01:12:54,103 --> 01:13:00,703
This swarm of worms and maggots Could have picked you to the bone!

633
01:13:00,903 --> 01:13:03,303
I know this man over here I know his name and his trade>>

634
01:13:03,303 --> 01:13:06,403
And on your witness, M'sieur, We'll see him suitably paid.

635
01:13:09,203 --> 01:13:12,603
But where's the gentleman gone? And why on earth did he run?

636
01:13:13,203 --> 01:13:19,503
You will have a job to find him He's not whom he seems to be>>

637
01:13:20,303 --> 01:13:28,703
And the girl who stood beside him is the child he stole from me. Yeah, and me.

638
01:13:29,903 --> 01:13:35,403
Could it be he's some old jailbird That the tide now washes in>>

639
01:13:35,603 --> 01:13:40,203
Heard my name and started running All the elements point to him>>

640
01:13:40,403 --> 01:13:51,303
In the absence of a victim, Dear Inspector, may I go?

641
01:13:54,503 --> 01:14:07,603
And remember when you've nicked him, It was me who told you so!

642
01:14:07,903 --> 01:14:15,603
Let the old man keep on running I will run him off his feet!

643
01:14:18,203 --> 01:14:22,403
Everyone about your business! Clear this garbage off the street!

644
01:14:22,603 --> 01:14:24,603
22."Éponine's Errand" (Éponine, Marius)>>

645
01:14:24,603 --> 01:14:34,203
Cosette! Now I remember! Cosette! How can it be?

646
01:14:35,203 --> 01:14:45,103
We were children together Look what's become of me...>>

647
01:14:48,103 --> 01:14:50,503
Eponine, who was that girl? Some bourgeois two-a-penny thing!

648
01:14:50,703 --> 01:14:57,403
Eponine, find her for me! What will you give me?

649
01:14:57,603 --> 01:14:58,903
Anything!

650
01:14:59,103 --> 01:15:03,603
Got you all excited now, But God knows what you see in her>>

651
01:15:03,803 --> 01:15:11,303
Ain't you all delighted now? No, I don't want your money sir...>>

652
01:15:13,603 --> 01:15:20,403
Eponine! Do this for me... Discover where she lives>>

653
01:15:20,603 --> 01:15:25,703
But careful how you go Don't let your father know>>

654
01:15:26,503 --> 01:15:31,403
'Ponine! I'm lost until she's found!

655
01:15:32,603 --> 01:15:39,303
You see, I told you so! There's lots of things I know>>

656
01:15:40,603 --> 01:15:51,403
'Ponine... she knows her way around!

657
01:15:51,800 --> 01:15:55,000
23."Red & Black" (The ABC Cafe, the students)>>

658
01:15:55,093 --> 01:15:57,813
The time is near>>

659
01:15:58,713 --> 01:16:02,813
So near it's stirring the blood in their veins!

660
01:16:03,013 --> 01:16:05,513
And yet beware>>

661
01:16:06,513 --> 01:16:11,213
Don't let the wine go to your brains!

662
01:16:11,413 --> 01:16:15,613
We need a sign To rally the people>>

663
01:16:15,813 --> 01:16:20,013
To call them to arms To bring them in line!

664
01:16:20,213 --> 01:16:21,713
Marius, wake up!

665
01:16:22,213 --> 01:16:25,813
What's wrong today? You look as if you've seen a ghost.

666
01:16:26,013 --> 01:16:29,213
Some wine and say what's going on!

667
01:16:29,413 --> 01:16:35,313
A ghost you say... a ghost maybe She was just like a ghost to me>>

668
01:16:35,513 --> 01:16:38,413
One minute there, and she was gone!

669
01:16:39,813 --> 01:16:43,013
I am agog! I am aghast!

670
01:16:43,213 --> 01:16:45,713
Is Marius in love at last?

671
01:16:45,913 --> 01:16:50,113
I've never heard him `ooh' and `aah'>>

672
01:16:50,913 --> 01:16:53,513
You talk of battles to be won>>

673
01:16:54,113 --> 01:16:56,613
And here he comes like Don Ju-an>>

674
01:16:56,813 --> 01:17:01,513
It's better than an o-per-a!

675
01:17:06,313 --> 01:17:11,013
It is time for us all To decide who we are>>

676
01:17:12,213 --> 01:17:16,813
Do we fight for the right To a night at the opera now?

677
01:17:17,613 --> 01:17:22,613
Have you asked of yourselves What's the price you might pay?

678
01:17:23,213 --> 01:17:27,313
Is it simply a game For rich young boys to play?

679
01:17:27,513 --> 01:17:34,013
The colors of the world are changing day by day...>>

680
01:17:34,513 --> 01:17:42,813
Red - the blood of angry men! Black - the dark of ages past!

681
01:17:43,013 --> 01:17:53,613
Red - a world about to dawn! Black - the night that ends at last!

682
01:17:53,813 --> 01:17:58,213
Had you seen here today You might know how it feels>>

683
01:17:58,413 --> 01:18:04,113
To be struck to the bone In a moment of breathless delight!

684
01:18:04,313 --> 01:18:08,013
Had you been there today You might also have known>>

685
01:18:09,613 --> 01:18:13,513
How the world may be changed In just one burst of light!

686
01:18:13,713 --> 01:18:20,913
And what was right seems wrong And what was wrong seems right!

687
01:18:21,113 --> 01:18:24,913
Red.. I feel my soul on fire!

688
01:18:25,113 --> 01:18:28,913
Black. My world if she's not there!

689
01:18:29,113 --> 01:18:32,513
Red.. The color of desire!

690
01:18:32,713 --> 01:18:37,713
Black... The color of despair!

691
01:18:38,113 --> 01:18:41,713
Marius, you're no longer a child I do not doubt you mean it well>>

692
01:18:41,913 --> 01:18:48,513
But now there is a higher call. Who cares about your lonely soul?

693
01:18:48,713 --> 01:18:54,813
We strive toward a larger goal Our little lives don't count at all!

694
01:18:55,313 --> 01:19:03,613
Red - the blood of angry men! Black - the dark of ages past!

695
01:19:04,013 --> 01:19:16,013
Red - a world about to dawn! Black - the night that ends at last!

696
01:19:16,013 --> 01:19:20,213
Listen everybody! Tell them that Lamarque is dead.

697
01:19:23,413 --> 01:19:28,313
Lamarque is dead. It's the hour of fate.

698
01:19:28,513 --> 01:19:37,913
The people's man. His death is the sign we await!

699
01:19:38,113 --> 01:19:40,413
On his funeral day they will honor his name.

700
01:19:40,613 --> 01:19:43,413
And the light of rebellion will be placed in their eyes.

701
01:19:43,613 --> 01:19:46,613
In the death of Lamarque we will kindle our flame>>

702
01:19:46,813 --> 01:19:50,113
In the 2 of the March shall oir barricades rise!

703
01:19:50,313 --> 01:19:52,313
The time is here!

704
01:19:52,513 --> 01:19:55,313
Let us welcome it gladly with courage and cheer>>

705
01:19:55,513 --> 01:19:58,513
Let us take to the streets with no doubt in our hearts>>

706
01:19:58,713 --> 01:20:00,113
But a jubilant shout>>

707
01:20:00,113 --> 01:20:02,713
They will come one and all>>

708
01:20:02,913 --> 01:20:09,713
They will come when we call!

709
01:20:19,800 --> 01:20:22,800
24."Rue Plumet / In My Life" (Cosette, Valjean, Marius, Éponine)>>

710
01:20:23,080 --> 01:20:28,400
How strange This feeling that my life's begun at last>>

711
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:34,800
This change, Can people really fall in love so fast?

712
01:20:35,500 --> 01:20:38,700
What's the matter with you, Cosette?

713
01:20:39,200 --> 01:20:42,000
Have you been too much on your own?

714
01:20:42,600 --> 01:20:50,400
So many things unclear So many things unknown.

715
01:20:52,200 --> 01:20:54,200
In my life>>

716
01:20:54,900 --> 01:21:00,000
There are so many questions and answers That somehow seem wrong>>

717
01:21:01,200 --> 01:21:02,900
In my life>>

718
01:21:02,900 --> 01:21:08,600
There are times when I catch in the silence The sigh of a faraway song>>

719
01:21:08,800 --> 01:21:10,300
And it sings>>

720
01:21:11,100 --> 01:21:14,900
Of a world that I long to see Out of reach>>

721
01:21:15,300 --> 01:21:19,500
Just a whisper away Waiting for me.

722
01:21:20,000 --> 01:21:23,900
Does he know I'm alive? Do I know if he's real?

723
01:21:24,500 --> 01:21:28,800
Does he see what I see? Does he feel what I feel?

724
01:21:29,600 --> 01:21:31,400
In my life>>

725
01:21:32,500 --> 01:21:37,700
I'm no longer alone Now the love in my life is so near>>

726
01:21:39,200 --> 01:21:45,000
Find me now, find me here!

727
01:21:49,100 --> 01:21:53,700
Dear Cosette, You're such a lonely child>>

728
01:21:54,200 --> 01:21:58,000
How pensive, how sad you seem to me>>

729
01:21:59,000 --> 01:22:03,500
Believe me, were it within my power>>

730
01:22:03,800 --> 01:22:06,900
I'd fill each passing hour>>

731
01:22:07,500 --> 01:22:11,500
How quiet it must be, I can see>>

732
01:22:11,900 --> 01:22:15,700
With only me for company.

733
01:22:17,200 --> 01:22:19,900
There's so little I know That I'm longing to know>>

734
01:22:19,900 --> 01:22:22,900
Of the man that you were In a time long ago...>>

735
01:22:23,900 --> 01:22:27,000
There's so little you say Of the life you have known>>

736
01:22:27,000 --> 01:22:30,300
Why you keep to yourself Why we're always alone>>

737
01:22:30,500 --> 01:22:37,300
So dark! So dark and deep... The secrets that you keep!

738
01:22:38,900 --> 01:22:40,600
In my life>>

