We'll fight like 20 armies And we won't give up>>

983
01:59:18,465 --> 01:59:26,365
So you'd better run for cover When the pup grows......>>

984
01:59:43,265 --> 01:59:46,465
33."The Final Battle" (Army officer, Students)>>

985
01:59:46,665 --> 01:59:49,065
You at the barricade listen to this>>

986
01:59:49,865 --> 01:59:53,365
The people of Paris sleep in their beds>>

987
01:59:53,565 --> 01:59:59,665
You have no chance No chance at all>>

988
02:00:00,565 --> 02:00:04,765
Why throw your lives away?

989
02:00:09,965 --> 02:00:16,765
Let us die facing our foes Make them bleed while we can>>

990
02:00:16,965 --> 02:00:20,765
Make 'em pay through the nose Make 'em pay for every man!

991
02:00:20,765 --> 02:00:31,865
Let others rise to take our place Until the earth is free!

993
02:04:58,668 --> 02:05:01,388
You're alive! I've saved you.

994
02:05:55,050 --> 02:05:57,670
It's you, Javert! I knew you wouldn't wait too long>>

995
02:05:58,270 --> 02:06:00,570
The faithful servant at his post once more!

996
02:06:01,170 --> 02:06:04,470
This man's done no wrong, And he needs a doctor's care.

997
02:06:05,732 --> 02:06:09,652
I warned you I would not give in I won't be swayed>>

998
02:06:09,652 --> 02:06:12,852
Another hour yet And then I'm yours>>

999
02:06:13,252 --> 02:06:16,452
And all our debts are paid.

1000
02:06:17,652 --> 02:06:22,252
The man of mercy comes again And talks of justice>>

1001
02:06:22,252 --> 02:06:27,552
Come, time is running short Look down, Javert>>

1002
02:06:28,052 --> 02:06:32,352
He's standing in his grave>>

1003
02:07:15,252 --> 02:07:18,452
34."Javert's Suicide" (Javert)>>

1004
02:07:18,809 --> 02:07:21,029
Who is this man? What sort of devil is he?

1005
02:07:21,029 --> 02:07:23,929
To have me caught in a trap And choose to let me go free?

1006
02:07:23,929 --> 02:07:26,629
It was his hour at last To put a seal on my fate,>>

1007
02:07:26,629 --> 02:07:29,329
Wipe out the past, And wash me clean off the slate.

1008
02:07:29,329 --> 02:07:32,329
All it would take was a flick of his knife.

1009
02:07:32,329 --> 02:07:36,229
Vengeance was his and he gave me back my life!

1010
02:07:38,229 --> 02:07:40,229
Damned if I'll live in the debt of a thief>>

1011
02:07:40,629 --> 02:07:42,829
Damned if I'll yield at the end of the chase>>

1012
02:07:43,029 --> 02:07:45,629
I am the Law and the Law is not mocked>>

1013
02:07:45,829 --> 02:07:47,829
I'll spit his pity right back in his face>>

1014
02:07:47,829 --> 02:07:50,529
There is nothing on earth that we share>>

1015
02:07:50,729 --> 02:07:53,629
It is either Valjean or Javert!

1016
02:07:59,829 --> 02:08:07,429
And my thoughts fly apart. Can this man be believed?

1017
02:08:08,229 --> 02:08:22,729
Shall his sins be forgiven? Shall his crimes be reprieved?

1018
02:08:22,929 --> 02:08:31,229
And must I now begin to doubt, Who never doubted all those years?

1019
02:08:32,229 --> 02:08:35,929
My heart is stone and still it trembles.

1020
02:08:36,229 --> 02:08:41,729
The world I have known is lost in shadow.

1021
02:08:42,229 --> 02:08:46,829
Is he from heaven or from hell?

1022
02:08:47,329 --> 02:08:54,729
And does he know That, granting me my life today,>>

1023
02:09:00,529 --> 02:09:07,229
This man has killed me even so?

1024
02:09:12,529 --> 02:09:21,929
I am reaching but I fall And the stars are black and cold>>

1025
02:09:22,829 --> 02:09:29,329
As I stare into the void Of a world that cannot hold>>

1026
02:09:29,729 --> 02:09:35,529
I'll escape now from that world From the world of Jean Valjean.

1027
02:09:35,829 --> 02:09:45,629
There is nowhere I can turn There is now way to go on...>>

1028
02:10:14,103 --> 02:10:19,123
Did you see them Going off to fight?

1029
02:10:19,323 --> 02:10:23,823
Children of the barricade Who didn't last the night?

1030
02:10:23,823 --> 02:10:28,423
Did you see them Lying where they died?

1031
02:10:28,623 --> 02:10:33,423
Someone used to cradle them And kiss them when they cried.

1032
02:10:33,723 --> 02:10:39,223
Did you see them lying side by side?

1033
02:10:44,023 --> 02:10:47,223
35."Empty Chairs at Empty Tables" (Marius)>>

1034
02:10:47,523 --> 02:10:50,823
There's a grief that can't be spoken.

1035
02:10:54,623 --> 02:10:57,923
There's a pain goes on and on.

1036
02:11:00,523 --> 02:11:04,423
Empty chairs at empty tables>>

1037
02:11:05,523 --> 02:11:11,623
Now my friends are dead and gone.

1038
02:11:14,623 --> 02:11:18,623
Here they talked of revolution>>

1039
02:11:20,523 --> 02:11:24,623
Here it was they lit the flame.

1040
02:11:26,423 --> 02:11:29,723
Here they sang about `tomorrow'>>

1041
02:11:31,423 --> 02:11:38,423
And tomorrow never came.

1042
02:11:40,923 --> 02:11:45,823
From the table in the corner>>

1043
02:11:46,423 --> 02:11:50,923
They could see a world reborn>>

1044
02:11:51,723 --> 02:12:01,223
And they rose with voices ringing I can hear them now!

1045
02:12:02,023 --> 02:12:06,423
The very words that they had sung>>

1046
02:12:07,323 --> 02:12:12,423
Became their last communion>>

1047
02:12:16,323 --> 02:12:19,323
On the lonely barricade at dawn.

1048
02:12:21,623 --> 02:12:30,423
Oh my friends, my friends forgive me>>

1049
02:12:32,023 --> 02:12:36,423
That I live and you are gone.

1050
02:12:36,823 --> 02:12:40,123
There's a grief that can't be spoken.

1051
02:12:40,823 --> 02:12:47,023
There's a pain goes on and on.

1052
02:12:47,223 --> 02:12:51,223
Phantom faces at the window.

1053
02:12:51,623 --> 02:12:56,323
Phantom shadows on the floor.

1054
02:12:56,523 --> 02:13:06,023
Empty chairs at empty tables Where my friends will meet no more.

1055
02:13:06,223 --> 02:13:14,123
Oh my friends, my friends, don't ask me>>

1056
02:13:14,323 --> 02:13:18,823
What your sacrifice was for>>

1057
02:13:19,923 --> 02:13:38,923
Empty chairs at empty tables Where my friends will sing no more.

1058
02:13:58,103 --> 02:14:01,303
36."Every Day / Heart Full of Love" (Marius, Cosette)>>

1059
02:14:01,601 --> 02:14:04,621
Every day you walk with stronger step>>

1060
02:14:04,821 --> 02:14:08,621
You walk with longer step- `The worst is over.'>>

1061
02:14:08,821 --> 02:14:12,821
Don't think about it, Marius! With all the years ahead of us!

1062
02:14:13,021 --> 02:14:17,921
I will never go away And we will be together>>

1063
02:14:18,121 --> 02:14:19,921
Every day.

1064
02:14:22,221 --> 02:14:31,221
Every day, we'll remember that night And the vow that we made:>>

1065
02:14:32,621 --> 02:14:44,121
A heart full of love A night full of you>>

1066
02:14:44,321 --> 02:14:47,321
The words are old But always true.

1067
02:14:47,521 --> 02:14:57,421
Cosette, Cosette! Waiting for you>>

1068
02:14:57,621 --> 02:14:59,921
At your feet>>

1069
02:15:04,421 --> 02:15:22,221
And it wasn't a dream Not a dream after all>>

1070
02:15:24,921 --> 02:15:28,121
M'sieur, this is a day I never can forget.

1071
02:15:29,321 --> 02:15:32,921
Is gratitude enough For giving me Cosette?

1072
02:15:33,821 --> 02:15:37,721
Your home shall be with us And not a day shall pass>>

1073
02:15:38,321 --> 02:15:41,821
But we will prove our love To you, whom we shall call>>

1074
02:15:41,821 --> 02:15:46,121
A father to us both A father to us all.

1075
02:15:46,321 --> 02:15:48,021
Not another word my son,>>

1076
02:15:50,821 --> 02:15:55,221
There's something now that must be done.

1077
02:15:58,121 --> 02:16:01,321
37."Valjean's Confession" (Valjean, Marius)>>

1078
02:16:01,521 --> 02:16:04,621
There lived a man whose hame was Jean Valjean>>

1079
02:16:08,721 --> 02:16:12,421
He stole some bread to save his sister's son.

1080
02:16:16,221 --> 02:16:20,421
For 19 winters served his time>>

1081
02:16:23,121 --> 02:16:27,221
In sweat he washed away his crime.

1082
02:16:29,421 --> 02:16:35,221
Years ago He broke parole and lived a life apart>>

1083
02:16:36,021 --> 02:16:39,121
How could he tell Cosette and break her heart?

1084
02:16:40,921 --> 02:16:45,321
It's for Cosette this must be faced If he is caught she is disgraced>>

1085
02:16:45,821 --> 02:16:54,921
The time has come to journey on And from this day he must be gone>>

1086
02:16:57,121 --> 02:17:03,421
Who am I?

1087
02:17:05,621 --> 02:17:09,521
You're Jean Valjean!

1088
02:17:10,721 --> 02:17:12,621
Monsieur, you cannot leave.

1089
02:17:13,221 --> 02:17:16,621
Whatever I tell my beloved Cosette She will never believe!

1090
02:17:18,721 --> 02:17:21,821
Tell her I have gone on a journey A long way away.

1091
02:17:22,521 --> 02:17:27,021
Tell her my heart was too full for farewells It is better this way.

1092
02:17:27,521 --> 02:17:33,421
Promise me, M'sieur, Cosette will never know... what I have spoken, why I must go.

1093
02:17:36,621 --> 02:17:45,621
For the sake of Cosette, it must be so.

1094
02:18:41,810 --> 02:18:44,930
38."Wedding Chorale" (Chorus)>>

1095
02:18:45,130 --> 02:18:50,730
Ring out the bells Upon this day of days!

1096
02:18:52,130 --> 02:18:57,630
May all the angels Of the Lord above>>

1097
02:19:00,230 --> 02:19:07,930
In jubilation Sing their songs of praise!

1098
02:19:08,930 --> 02:19:14,130
And crown this blessed time with Peace and love.

1099
02:19:14,351 --> 02:19:18,871
The Baron and Baroness de Thénard>>

1100
02:19:19,772 --> 02:19:26,370
Go away, Thénardier! Do you think I don't know who you are?

1101
02:19:26,670 --> 02:19:30,170
He's not fooled. Told you so.

1102
02:19:30,370 --> 02:19:36,170
Show M'sieur what you've come here to show. Tell the boy what you know!

1103
02:19:37,770 --> 02:19:44,770
Pity to disturb you at a feast like this But 500 francs surely wouldn't come amiss.

1104
02:19:44,970 --> 02:19:47,270
In God's name say what you have to say.

1105
02:19:47,470 --> 02:19:49,770
He speaks you pay!

1106
02:19:49,970 --> 02:19:58,170
What I saw, clear as light, Jean Valjean in the sewers one night.

1107
02:19:58,570 --> 02:20:05,070
Had this corpse on his back Some boy he had killed in a vicious attack.

1108
02:20:05,770 --> 02:20:13,470
I was there, never fear. Even found me this fine souvenir.

1109
02:20:14,370 --> 02:20:21,270
I know this! This was mine! This is surely some heavenly sign!

1110
02:20:21,470 --> 02:20:30,070
Then it's true. Then I'm right. Jean Valjean was my savior that night!

1111
02:20:30,770 --> 02:20:38,370
Jean Valjean, the old con. You pay up or I say where he's gone.

1112
02:20:38,570 --> 02:20:40,370
Where is he?

1113
02:20:44,570 --> 02:20:46,770
Where is he? The convent.

1114
02:20:48,670 --> 02:20:51,070
39."Beggars at the Feast" (Thénardier and Mme.)>>

1115
02:20:51,070 --> 02:20:53,870
Watch the buggers dance Watch 'em till they drop>>

1116
02:20:54,070 --> 02:20:56,870
Keep your wits about you And you stand on top!

1117
02:20:57,070 --> 02:20:59,670
Masters of the land Always get our share>>

1118
02:20:59,870 --> 02:21:02,470
Clear away the barricades And we're still there!

1119
02:21:02,670 --> 02:21:07,770
We know where the wind is blowing Money is the stuff we smell.

1120
02:21:07,970 --> 02:21:12,170
And when we're rich as Croesus Jesus! Won't we see you all in hell!

1121
02:21:21,770 --> 02:21:24,970
40."Valjean's Death" (Valjean, Fantine, Cosette, Marius, Bishop of Digne)>>

1122
02:21:28,470 --> 02:21:36,670
Alone I wait in the shadows I count the hours untill I sleep>>

1123
02:21:38,870 --> 02:21:47,870
I dreamed a dream Cosette stood by It made her weep to know I die.

1124
02:21:53,470 --> 02:22:01,570
Alone at the end of the day Upon this wedding night I pray>>

1125
02:22:03,370 --> 02:22:17,570
Take these children, my Lord, to thy embrace And show them grace.

1126
02:22:20,570 --> 02:22:32,870
God on high Hear my prayer>>

1127
02:22:37,470 --> 02:22:45,370
Take me now To thy care>>

1128
02:22:48,870 --> 02:22:58,370
Where You are Let me be>>

1129
02:23:02,470 --> 02:23:11,270
Take me now Take me there>>

1130
02:23:14,470 --> 02:23:26,270
Bring me home>>

1131
02:23:28,770 --> 02:23:41,570
M'sieur, I bless your name M'sieur, lay down your burden>>

1132
02:23:44,270 --> 02:23:57,370
You raised my child in love And you will be with god.

1133
02:24:04,970 --> 02:24:11,170
Papa, Papa, I do not understand! Are you alright? Why did you go away?

1134
02:24:13,970 --> 02:24:20,370
Cosette, my child, am I forgiven now? Thank God, thank God, I've lived to see this day.

1135
02:24:20,570 --> 02:24:28,070
It's you who must forgive a thoughtless fool It's you who must forgive a thankless man>>

1136
02:24:28,970 --> 02:24:37,070
It's thanks to you that I am living And again I lay down my life at your feet.

1137
02:24:37,470 --> 02:24:40,770
Cosette, your father is a saint.

1138
02:24:41,470 --> 02:24:46,970
When they wounded me He took me from the barricade>>

1139
02:24:47,170 --> 02:24:56,670
Carried like a babe And brought me home to you!

1140
02:25:06,970 --> 02:25:17,470
Now you are here Again beside me>>

1141
02:25:21,070 --> 02:25:30,770
Now I can die in peace For now my life is blessed...>>

1142
02:25:32,070 --> 02:25:42,970
You will live, Papa, you're going to live It's too soon, too soon to say goodbye!

1143
02:25:43,670 --> 02:25:57,870
Yes, Cosette, forbid me now to die I'll obey, I will try.

1144
02:25:59,770 --> 02:26:07,770
On this page I write my last confession.

1145
02:26:10,670 --> 02:26:16,970
Read it well When I at last am sleeping.

1146
02:26:20,070 --> 02:26:26,670
It's the story Of one who turned from hating.

1147
02:26:27,570 --> 02:26:34,270
A man who only learned to love with you and his keeping.

1148
02:26:37,070 --> 02:26:45,970
Come with me Where chains will never bind you>>

1149
02:26:46,670 --> 02:26:54,070
All your grief At last, at last behind you.

1150
02:26:55,370 --> 02:27:03,570
Lord in Heaven, Look down on him in mercy.

1151
02:27:03,770 --> 02:27:10,070
Forgive me all my trespasses And take me to your glory.

1152
02:27:12,470 --> 02:27:21,670
Take my hand I'll lead you to salvation.

1153
02:27:22,370 --> 02:27:30,070
Take my love, For love is everlasting.

1154
02:27:31,370 --> 02:27:39,170
And remember The truth that once was spoken>>

1155
02:27:39,770 --> 02:27:52,970
To love another person Is to see the face of God!

1156
02:27:53,170 --> 02:27:57,470
41."Do You Hear the People Sing?" (The Cast) Lost in the valley of the night?

1157
02:27:57,670 --> 02:28:03,470
It is the music of a people Who are climbing to the light.

1158
02:28:03,670 --> 02:28:09,870
For the wretched of the earth There is a flame that never dies.

1159
02:28:10,070 --> 02:28:15,670
Even the darkest night will end And the sun will rise.

1160
02:28:15,934 --> 02:28:22,654
They will live again in freedom In the garden of the Lord.

1161
02:28:22,854 --> 02:28:28,654
They will walk behind the plough-share, They will put away the sword.

1162
02:28:28,854 --> 02:28:34,154
The chain will be broken And all men will have their reward.

1163
02:28:34,454 --> 02:28:40,454
Will you join in our crusade? Who will be strong and stand with me?

1164
02:28:40,654 --> 02:28:46,454
Somewhere beyond the barricade Is there a world you long to see?

1165
02:28:46,654 --> 02:28:52,354
Do you hear the people sing? Say, do you hear the distant drums?

1166
02:28:52,554 --> 02:28:58,254
It is the future that they bring When tomorrow comes!

1167
02:28:58,454 --> 02:29:04,354
Will you join in our crusade? Who will be strong and stand with me?

1168
02:29:04,554 --> 02:29:10,154
Somewhere beyond the barricade Is there a world you long to see?

1169
02:29:10,354 --> 02:29:16,054
Do you hear the people sing? Say, do you hear the distant drums?

1170
02:29:16,254 --> 02:29:22,254
It is the future that they bring When tomorrow comes...>>

